LONCHURA was hustled from the gate, pressed the pace on the outside, vied four then three wide on the turn, dropped back into upper stretch, remained on her inside lead in the drive and tired. GRAM was hustled from the start, showed speed between foes then dropped back nearing the half-mile pole, went three then two wide on the turn, turned into upper stretch under a drive and came up empty. SWEPT broke in and bumped with a foe, was urged along on the outside, went five wide on the turn and capitulated.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: BELMONT PARK RACE 2 1M Turf CR: 81. Claiming Purse 48000. (UP TO $8,352 NYSBFOA) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Claiming Price $50,000 (1.5% Afterc are Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void). (If the Stewards consider it inadvisable to run this race on the turf course, this race will be run at One Mile on the Main Track.) (Rail at 18 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KANNON FIRE just off the inside tracking the leader in closest aim, advanced through the far turn latching on SARATOGA GAZE midway, spun two to three wide into upper stretch, rallied to take command a furlong out and drifted out under left handed encouragement and crosses with the left rein only, forced PEGS A. K. GIRL to pause and alter course a sixteenth out, continued coming out to the finish and held safe to prevail. PEGS A. K. GIRL tracked the pace along the inside patiently handled until set down spinning three wide into upper stretch, rallied offering up a mild kick and had KANNON FIRE drift out directly in front nearing the sixteenth pole and was paused and altered inwards losing about a half length of momentum and latched on the winner near the finish while along clear for the place honors. SARATOGA GAZE showed the way rated on the pace along the inside, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, cut the corner into upper stretch, dug in under threat and was collared nearing the eighth pole, kept on to preserve the show honors. WESTERN LANE saved ground near the rear of the field, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch and improved position to the finish. SNOW LOVES A FIGHT two to three wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, offered up a bid swinging four wide into upper stretch, then flattened out in the drive. FROSTY INVASION chased two to three wide coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, angled four wide into upper stretch, came up empty. DUCKPHAT chased along the inside until tipped to the two path placed to coaxing at the three-eighths, angled five wide into upper stretch and trailed. There was a Stewards' Inquiry into the stretch run as well as a claim of foul by the trainer of PEGS A. K. GIRL alleging interference from KANNON FIRE in the stretch. After review, it was deemed that KANNON FIRE had not interfered with PEGS A. K. GIRL and the result was allowed to stand prior to the race being declared official. Please note a head on shot of the starting gate was unavailable in the replays so any possible trouble at the start was unable to be viewed.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BERNT AGAIN dropped from the two path to the rail on the first turn, was reserved off the pace, shifted from the rail to the two path early on the far turn, came out three wide and bumped a foe near the five-sixteenths, rallied to make a bid into the stretch, fought with rivals to near the eighth-pole, dueled inside of the runner-up into the final sixteenth and proved best under strong urging. ORANGE FREEZE was taken under a tight hold while four wide on the first turn, raced on the outside under reserve, moved closer while shifting from three to five wide on the far turn, gained to make a bid into the stretch, fought with two foes until near the furlong marker, dueled with the winner into the final sixteenth and was outfinished while able to get the place. KARA PARA dropped back in the two path on the first turn, was reserved towards the back, moved closer in the two path on the far turn, was roused four wide into the stretch, chased the top two in the drive and finished with good courage for the show. LEM ME DRINK saved ground going around the opening bend, bobbled near the seven-eighths, was rated just off the pace, drafted inside on the far turn, was asked once straightened for the drive, pursued the leaders while off the rail in the stretch and lacked the needed kick. SHOPPINGATBLOOMIES broke out but came out in front, showed the way on the inside, was asked near the quarter-pole, lost the lead into upper stretch, dropped back outside the furlong marker and gave way. DENIECE OF DEGRACE went five then four wide on the first turn, settled towards the rear, dropped from the three path to the rail on the far turn and lacked the needed response. MY JUNE BUG was backed out of the gate and reloaded then hustled from the start, raced in the three path on the first turn, stalked the pace on the outside, chased in the two path on the far turn, dropped back into the stretch and capitulated. DERWIN'S PAYNTER was off a step slow, rounded the first turn in the two path, lagged at the rear, went three to five wide on the far turn and failed to threaten. WAR MUSEUM was taken under a tight hold in the three path on the first turn then rated off the pace, went three wide early on the far turn then was bumped four wide around the five-sixteenths, dropped back five wide into the stretch and had nothing left. MIDNIGHT EMPRESS was fractious in the gate, went five wide on the first turn, was rated just off the pace on the outside without cover, came up empty while four then three wide on the far turn and faltered then was pulled up in the stretch then vanned off.
